This paper discusses the digital signal processing and circuit architectures for Massive MIMO, which is a wireless communication technology. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of information and communication. The paper also discusses the hardware implementation of Massive MIMO, which falls under the categories of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper discusses energy efficiency, which is a topic that falls under the category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
